what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
Odyssey is working with one of the Gulf's premier Government hospitals to source an experienced Specialist in Paediatric Emergency Medicine to join a team of Consultants, Specialists and Residents providing Emergency Care in Abu Dhabi under the supervision of Consultants in ER. The hospital holds accreditation with several major international organisations including the Joint Commission International (JCI) and the medical services provided are of North American standard. The position offers a challenging clinical environment with educational responsibilities and scope for academic work. The remuneration package is attractive and tax free at source.
You must hold the MD or MBBS degree and have completed a postgraduate residency programme in Paediatrics or Emergency Medicine and gained an appropriate qualification listed in Tier 1, 2 or 3 of the HAAD PQR (see attached). You must hold the experience listed for your qualification working in ER and preferably in a hospital affiliated with an University. You must be fluent in written and spoken English and have a sound understanding of JCI policies and EHR.
To apply please send a detailed CV with employment history.
